[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Since 1903, all tires, tubes, valves, and rims have followed standards established by the Tire & Rim Association of America (T&RA). Such a move benefits manufacturers, farmers, and growers in the way they source tires and fit their equipment.\n\nThe European market would also follow this model, with the European Tyre and Rim Technical Organization’s (ERTRO) creation in the 1960s. ERTRO standardized pneumatic tires and rims in the same way as the T&RA, providing a benchmark for the industries to follow.\n\nEach size that manufacturers develop must fall within the following tolerance for any given tire size in millimeters or inches:\n"},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"bulleted_list_item","bulleted_list_item":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Tire Overall Diameter (O.D.) = + / - 2% versus the Industry Size Standard"},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"bulleted_list_item","bulleted_list_item":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Tire Section Width (S.W.) = + / - 4% versus the Industry Size Standard"},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"\nIn addition to the above design limits, there are other considerations that affect tire design and construction. For example, tire dimensions can change simply from the tire’s type and construction whether standard, IF, or VF. Other design challenges and considerations include:\n\n"},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"heading_2","heading_2":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Tread Depth"},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"bulleted_list_item","bulleted_list_item":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"The tire tread depth based on the lug design affects the overall diameter (OD) of a standard R-1 pattern versus the same sized tire with deeper R-1W, or R-2 tread depth."},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"bulleted_list_item","bulleted_list_item":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Tire tread depth will also differ from manufacturer to manufacturer which will affect the tire geometry despite tires being of the same size and within the above industry tolerances."},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"heading_2","heading_2":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Tire Weight"},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"bulleted_list_item","bulleted_list_item":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"In addition, tire weight is not mandated in the standard beyond the above dimensional requirements, therefore the type of tire or materials used will affect the deflection and geometry of the tire under load."},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"heading_2","heading_2":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Tire Inflation"},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"bulleted_list_item","bulleted_list_item":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Specifically, in bias ply tires, the different ply rating or load ratings of the same size can result in different inflated overall diameter (OD) based on a given air pressure/tire load."},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"bulleted_list_item","bulleted_list_item":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Radial tires with a steel belt package or belts may have different inflated OD from the same size tire with nylon breakers."},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"heading_2","heading_2":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Construction and Design"},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"bulleted_list_item","bulleted_list_item":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Lug design can also influence how the tire under load compares to the industry standard when fully inflated."},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"bulleted_list_item","bulleted_list_item":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Bead and sidewall optimization by each manufacturer can impact the type and width of the rim recommended that could deviate from the industry standard as an alternative rim fitment."},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Using MAXAM’s very own AgriXtra85 VF tire, let’s look at how the tire compares with the organization’s standard:"},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false}}]}},{"object":"block","type":"table","table":{"table_width":9,"has_column_header":true,"has_row_header":false},"children":[{"object":"block","type":"table_row","table_row":{"cells":[[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Tire Size"},"